Titolo: Quantum (video game)

Anno: 1982

Descrizione: Quantum is a color vector arcade video game developed at General Computer Corporation for Atari Inc. and released in December 1982. It was designed by Betty Ryan (n√©e Tylko) who was the first female developer at GCC. The premise of the game is related loosely to quantum physics; the player directs a probe with a trackball to encircle atomic "particles" for points, without touching various other particles. Once the particles are  surrounded by the probe's tail they are destroyed.